Synthetic re-construction of upstream bug fix
aba8a62f9893f0ba18ec11fc2dc6d6983a2896b6 ("Fix F2Poly.signum").

The original buggy F2Poly.signum was `id`, returning the input
polynomial unchanged. The fix returns the constant 1 polynomial for any
non-zero input. The original commit hand-coded a `Bit True` singleton;
modern HEAD uses a pre-defined `one` value, so this synthetic patch
re-introduces the `id` form against modern HEAD.

Reverse-applying installs the bug; forward-applying restores the fix.

diff --git a/src/Data/Bit/F2Poly.hs b/src/Data/Bit/F2Poly.hs
--- a/src/Data/Bit/F2Poly.hs
+++ b/src/Data/Bit/F2Poly.hs
@@ -105,7 +105,7 @@ instance Num F2Poly where
 instance Num F2Poly where
   (+) = coerce xorBits
   (-) = coerce xorBits
   negate = id
   abs    = id
-  signum = id
+  signum = const one
   (*) = coerce ((dropWhileEnd .) . karatsuba)
   fromInteger !n = case n of
     IS i#
